    "plan_content": "## Plan: Add `extensions/pulseboard/` — 7 New Files\n\nHere's what I found and how the implementation will work:\n\n---\n\n### Key findings from codebase exploration\n\n**Pattern reference**: The Nostr extension (`extensions/nostr/`) is the closest analogue — it's a simpler plugin with flat outbound adapter, minimal config, and no third-party runtime deps. IRC is more complex and not the right template here.\n\n**Critical constraint — `getChatChannelMeta`**: This function takes a `ChatChannelId` — a strict union of *registered* core channel IDs read from bundled plugin manifests at startup. Since \"pulseboard\" isn't in the core registry, calling `getChatChannelMeta(\"pulseboard\")` would be a TypeScript error. The fix: import the function per the requirement, but build the `meta` object as an inline literal (exactly what Nostr does with its own meta).\n\n**`ChannelConfigAdapter<T>`**: Only two fields are *required* — `listAccountIds` and `resolveAccount`. Everything else (`isConfigured`, `describeAccount`, etc.) is optional.\n\n**`ChannelSetupAdapter`**: Only `applyAccountConfig` is required.\n\n**`ResolvedPulseBoardAccount`**: `createChatChannelPlugin<TResolvedAccount>` requires `TResolvedAccount extends { accountId?: string | null }`. The `PulseBoardAccount` interface in `types.ts` doesn't include `accountId`, so we define an inline `ResolvedPulseBoardAccount` type in `channel.ts` that extends `PulseBoardAccount` with `accountId`.\n\n**`sendText` result**: Use `attachChannelToResult(\"pulseboard\", { to, messageId })` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-send-result` — same as Nostr.\n\n---\n\n### Files to create\n\n| File | Notes |\n|---|---|\n| `extensions/pulseboard/package.json` | `@openclaw/pulseboard`, `type: \"module\"`, `openclaw` block with all 5 channel fields |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json` | `id`, `channels`, minimal `configSchema` |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts` | 3 interfaces: `PulseBoardAccount`, `PulseBoardConfig`, `PulseBoardMessage` |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>` → exports `getPulseBoardRuntime`, `setPulseBoardRuntime` |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/src/channel.ts` | Full plugin via `createChatChannelPlugin`, inline meta, stub adapters, flat outbound |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry` (Nostr pattern, no cast needed) |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin)` |\n\n**No existing files are modified.** Verification: `pnpm tsgo` + `pnpm check` + `git diff --stat` shows only new files.",
